# UI Rules

See full spec: `docs/ui-rules.md`

## Primitives — React Native Only

| Use | Instead of |
|-----|------------|
| `<View>` | `<div>` |
| `<Text>` | `<span>` / `<p>` |
| `<Pressable>` | `<button>` / `<a>` |
| `<FlatList>` | `ScrollView + .map()` |

## Styling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { padding: spacing.md, backgroundColor: colors.surface },
});

// ❌ BAD
<View style={{ padding: 16, backgroundColor: '#fff' }} />
```

- Spacing: multiples of 4 only — use `spacing.*` constants
- Colors: always `colors.*` tokens — never raw hex
- Typography: always `typography.*` scale — min 16px body, min 12px any text

## Touch Targets

```typescript
// Min 44×44pt — use hitSlop when visual is smaller
<Pressable
  hitSlop={{ top: 8, bottom: 8, left: 8, right: 8 }}
  style={({ pressed }) => [styles.btn, pressed && styles.pressed]}
  onPress={onPress}
/>
```

## App header / brand mark (React Native)

- **Logo-only headers:** use a flat layout (no pill/chip around the mark unless the design system calls for it). Prefer `resizeMode="contain"`, fixed **height** aligned to adjacent controls (e.g. same `minHeight` as wallet/search chips), and a **max width** so wide wordmarks do not collide with trailing actions.
- Give the image a clear **`accessibilityLabel`** (e.g. product name). If you add depth, use a light **shadow/elevation** on a wrapper `View`, not a heavy border that reads as a second button.
- Keep **touch targets** for real controls ≥44×44pt; decorative logos do not need to be pressable unless they navigate home.

## Custom bottom tab bar (React Native)

- Keep **≥12pt** for tab labels where possible; use `adjustsFontSizeToFit` + `minimumFontScale` (e.g. 0.8–0.85) and `numberOfLines={1}` so full labels stay on one line on narrow widths without defaulting to tiny body text.
- Tighten **horizontal padding** on the bar and between pill/icon/label first; avoid shrinking touch targets below **44×44pt** — use **`hitSlop`** on `Pressable` when visuals are compact.
- **Icon-only** inactive tabs still need **`accessibilityLabel`** (or `tabBarAccessibilityLabel`) so VoiceOver is not silent.
- Prefer **`options.title`** / **`tabBarLabel`** for visible tab copy — do not show raw route keys (e.g. `App/Home`) in the UI.

## Lists

```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use FlatList for dynamic data
const renderItem = useCallback(({ item }) => <ItemCard item={item} />, []);
<FlatList data={items} keyExtractor={i => i.id} renderItem={renderItem} />
```

## Safe Areas

```typescript
import { SafeAreaView } from 'react-native-safe-area-context';
// Always wrap root screens — never place fixed bars without safe area insets
```

## Accessibility

- `accessibilityLabel` + `accessibilityRole` on all interactive elements
- No emoji icons — vector icons only (`@expo/vector-icons` or `react-native-vector-icons`)
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 (text), 3:1 (large text / icons)

## Animation

- **Use React Native’s built-in `Animated` API** (`import { Animated } from 'react-native'`) for all UI motion — timing, spring, stagger, `Animated.event`, etc.
- Prefer **`useNativeDriver: true`** whenever the animated style uses only `opacity` and/or `transform` (composite props).
- Duration: 150–300ms; max 400ms for complex transitions
- Only animate `opacity` and `transform` — never `width`/`height` on the UI thread without a strong reason
- Respect reduced motion: `AccessibilityInfo.isReduceMotionEnabled()` — skip or shorten motion and apply end state immediately
- Do not introduce other animation libraries for standard transitions unless the team explicitly adopts them project-wide

## Empty / Loading / Error States

```typescript
if (isLoading) return <SkeletonList />;
if (error)     return <ErrorState onRetry={refetch} />;
if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState message="No data yet." />;
```
